Class SharedAccessQueuePolicy

  • java.lang.Object

  • public final class SharedAccessQueuePolicy

      • permissionsToString

        public java.lang.String permissionsToString​()
        Converts this policy's permissions to a string.
        Specified by:
        permissionsToString in class SharedAccessPolicy
        Returns:
        A String that represents the shared access permissions in the "raup" format, which is described at setPermissionsFromString(String).

      • setPermissionsFromString

        public void setPermissionsFromString​(java.lang.String value)
        Sets shared access permissions using the specified permissions string.
        Specified by:
        setPermissionsFromString in class SharedAccessPolicy
        Parameters:
        value - A String that represents the shared access permissions. The string must contain one or more of the following values. Note that they must be lower case, and the order that they are specified must be in the order of "raup".
        • d: Read access.
        • l: Add access.
        • r: Update access.
        • w: ProcessMessages access.
